Package com.linkedin.venice.meta

Interface Version

All Superinterfaces:
Comparable<Version>, DataModelBackedStructure<StoreVersion>
All Known Implementing Classes:
ReadOnlyStore.ReadOnlyVersion, ReadOnlyViewStore.ReadOnlyMaterializedViewVersion, VersionImpl
public interface Version extends Comparable<Version>, DataModelBackedStructure<StoreVersion>
This interface defines all the public APIs, and if you need to add accessors to some new fields, this interface needs to be changed accordingly.

      static boolean isKillableSystemPush(String pushId)
      Check if the push ID represents a system-initiated push that can be killed by user-initiated pushes. This includes regular repushes and compliance pushes.
      Parameters:
      pushId - the push job ID to check
      Returns:
      true if the push is a killable system push

    • canIncomingPushKillExistingPush

      static boolean canIncomingPushKillExistingPush(String existingPushJobId, String incomingPushJobId, Version.PushType incomingPushType)
      Determine if an existing push job can be killed by an incoming push job. An existing push can be killed if: 1. The existing push is a killable system push (repush or compliance push), AND 2. The incoming push is NOT an incremental push, AND 3. The incoming push is NOT itself a killable system push (i.e., it's a user-initiated push) This allows user-initiated batch pushes to preempt system-initiated pushes like repushes and compliance pushes, but prevents system pushes from killing each other.
      Parameters:
      existingPushJobId - the push job ID of the currently running push
      incomingPushJobId - the push job ID of the new push attempting to start
      incomingPushType - the type of the incoming push
      Returns:
      true if the existing push can be killed to allow the incoming push to proceed
